Canadian Version:

        I've done a little checking, and the story for Canadians
        appears to be this:

        (a) The RSA patents do not apply in Canada, so PGP should not
            present any problems wrt use and distribution.

        (b) Canada has a "monkey-see-monkey-do" pact with the USA wrt
            export controls, so it would not do to send PGP out of the
            country.

        (c) As in the USA, there is nothing preventing its import
            from Europe (eg. ghost or garbo).

    The usual caveat about getting your own lawyer applies...

    Cheers,
                Marc

